## Utility: Relative Time Formatting

Create a utility for formatting timestamps as relative time ("2 hours ago", "just now", etc.).

**File: `apps/dashboard/src/lib/format.ts`**

```typescript
export function formatRelativeTime(dateString: string): string {
  const date = new Date(dateString);
  const now = new Date();
  const diffMs = now.getTime() - date.getTime();
  const diffSeconds = Math.floor(diffMs / 1000);
  const diffMinutes = Math.floor(diffSeconds / 60);
  const diffHours = Math.floor(diffMinutes / 60);
  const diffDays = Math.floor(diffHours / 24);

  if (diffSeconds < 60) return "just now";
  if (diffMinutes < 60) return `${diffMinutes}m ago`;
  if (diffHours < 24) return `${diffHours}h ago`;
  if (diffDays < 7) return `${diffDays}d ago`;
  return date.toLocaleDateString();
}
```

---

## GitHub App Installation Flow

The "Connect Repo" button links to the GitHub App installation URL. This URL is:

```
https://github.com/apps/{app-slug}/installations/new
```

After the user installs the app on a repository, GitHub redirects back to the dashboard with a callback URL. The callback handler (implemented in Phase 3) creates the project record or updates the installation.

The URL is stored in the `NEXT_PUBLIC_GITHUB_APP_INSTALL_URL` environment variable so it is available in the client-side code.

---

## Environment Variables Required

| Variable | Purpose | Example |
|----------|---------|---------|
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_GITHUB_APP_INSTALL_URL` | GitHub App installation URL for "Connect Repo" button | `https://github.com/apps/gblockparty/installations/new` |

---

## Responsive Breakpoints

| Breakpoint | Grid Columns | Card Width |
|-----------|-------------|-----------|
| Default (mobile) | 1 column | Full width |
| `sm` (640px+) | 2 columns | ~50% |
| `lg` (1024px+) | 3 columns | ~33% |

Tailwind classes: `grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3`

